description.narrative: MTR - COs' and ROs' capacity strengthened to support policies,programmes and advocacy to strengthen child protection systems that support children affected by violence, prevent unnecessary family separation and enable children's access to justice, which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Protect Every Child from Violence and Exploitation By 2021, UNICEF supported countries apply relevant policies, innovative approaches and evidence, to design and implement publicly and privately funded development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that Protect Every Child from Violence and Exploitation

description.narrative: UNICEF led global efforts to establish inclusive and effective Child Protection Systems to prevent and respond to child protection violations by promoting partnerships, building consensus/capacities internally across sectors and externally amongst stakeholders, and accelerating country level operationalization to further mitigate the impact of COVID-19 pandemic. As follow-up to the CPSSEvaluation, UNICEF issuedguidanceon UNICEF’s approach to CPSS describing the programme-impact pathways and 7 intermediate outcomes for CPSS, high-impact CPSS interventions, and benchmarks to track progress and measure impact of UNICEF’s CPSS work. UNICEF launched theReimagine Justice for Children Agendaat theWorld Congress on Justice with Children. | Status:Met | As-of Date:04/03/2022
